{"id":13343,"date":"2020-08-09T15:57:58","date_gmt":"2020-08-09T22:57:58","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=13343"},"modified":"2020-08-09T15:58:58","modified_gmt":"2020-08-09T22:58:58","slug":"lade-slipper-trail-to-goat-mountain","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2020\/08\/09\/lade-slipper-trail-to-goat-mountain\/","title":{"rendered":"LADE SLIPPER TRAIL to GOAT MOUNTAIN"},"content":{"rendered":"<header class=\"fusion-header-wrapper fusion-is-sticky\">\n<div class=\"fusion-header-v1 fusion-logo-alignment fusion-logo-left fusion-sticky-menu-1 fusion-sticky-logo-1 fusion-mobile-logo-1 fusion-mobile-menu-design-modern\">\n<div class=\"fusion-header fusion-sticky-shadow\">\n<div class=\"fusion-row\">\n<nav class=\"fusion-main-menu fusion-sticky-menu\" aria-label=\"Main Menu Sticky\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em>The Lady Slipper trail leads to the summit of Goat Mountain. The summit is a lovely meadow without views.\u00a0<\/em><\/span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Location:<\/strong> Goat Mountain is the mountain to the NE of Creston.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Difficulty:<\/strong> B1 moderate<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Elevation Gain<\/strong>: 400m<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Distance:<\/strong> 4.8km round trip<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Time:<\/strong> 3 hours<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Season:<\/strong> Spring to fall<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Access<\/strong>: Copious parking but make sure to be well off the road.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Map:<\/strong> 82F\/2<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Drive:<\/strong> Turn off Lakeview-Arrow Creek Rd onto Foster Rd and continue along the FSR for a half hour or so until you see the marked trailhead on your left.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span class=\"menu-text\"><strong>Trail:<\/strong> This<\/span>\u00a0well-forested trail ascends the side of Goat Mountain to its summit \u2013 a lush and mossy mountaintop meadow nestled between\u00a0swaying conifers. For a view, head down to the right just a few meters before the summit.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/nav>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/header>\n<div class=\"fusion-row\">\n<section id=\"content\">\n<div id=\"post-10470\" class=\"post-10470 page type-page status-publish hentry\">\n<div class=\"post-content\">\n<div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-1 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\">\n<div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row \">\n<div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion_builder_column_3_5 fusion-builder-column-2 fusion-three-fifth fusion-column-last 3_5\">\n<div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper\" data-bg-url=\"\">\n<div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-builder-row-inner fusion-row \">\n<div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion_builder_column_2_3 fusion-two-third fusion-column-last 2_3\">\n<div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-column-wrapper-2\" data-bg-url=\"\">\n<div class=\"fusion-text\">\n<div id=\"boxed-wrapper\">\n<div id=\"wrapper\" class=\"fusion-wrapper\">\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>References:\u00a0<\/strong><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">https:\/\/www.crestonvalleytrails.ca\/trails\/ladyslipper-trail\/<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><a href=\"http:\/\/crestoncommunityforest.co